plot: Weeks out from the 2020 presidential election, John takes a look at various efforts to destabilize the vote, how to ensure your ballot is properly counted, and why in this election the election night should be considered an election month.

As the US 2020 presidential election is just around the corner, John Oliver takes a dive into changed aspects of the election because of the pandemic. He also suggests what can be done by a concerned citizen during the difficult times and when to expect to find out the final outcome of the election.—Niaz Islam Arif
